cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image processing and segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The use of 3D CNNs and dilated convolutions also suggests that it may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of lightweight networks and reducing computational cost may indicate that it could also be classified under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of the BraTS-2018 challenge dataset suggests that it may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
